==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jute
<hw>Jute</hw> <pr>(j⟦umac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>j⟦umac⟧t</ets>, Skr. <ets>j⟦umac⟧⟦tsdot⟧a</ets> matted hair; cf.
<ets>ja⟦tsdot⟧a</ets> matted hair, fibrous roots.]</ety> <def>The
coarse, strong fiber of the East Indian <spn>Corchorus olitorius</spn>,
and <spn>Corchorus capsularis</spn>; also, the plant itself. The fiber
is much used for making mats, gunny cloth, cordage, hangings, paper,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jutes</ent>⟦br⟧
